Create a detached working tree (https://stackoverflow.com/questions/12450245/getting-a-working-copy-of-a-bare-repository)

git init --bare

git config core.bare false
git config core.worktree /somewhere/else/

git checkout -f

Copy a single file from a repository (https://unix.stackexchange.com/questions/97371/copy-a-single-file-from-local-git-repository)

git archive --remote=file:///path/to/repository.git HEAD:path/to/directory filename | tar -x

dependencies:
 - git
 - tar
